Wiki processing complete. Here's what was done:

## Papers Processed (3)

1. **2604.10866 - OccuBench**: Agent evaluation benchmark using Language Environment Simulators (LES) to test AI agents across 65 professional domains (healthcare, finance, legal, etc.). Key finding: implicit faults (silent data truncation) cause larger drops than explicit errors (HTTP 500s) because agents lack error signals to trigger re-query.

2. **2604.15308 - RAD-2**: Generator-discriminator RL framework for autonomous driving motion planning. Diffusion generator produces trajectory candidates; RL discriminator evaluates them based on long-term outcomes. Uses TC-GRPO for credit assignment and BEV-Warp for high-throughput simulation. 56% collision rate reduction.

3. **2604.16044 - SNR-t Bias**: Identifies that DPMs suffer from Signal-to-Noise Ratio-timestep bias during inference — predicted sample SNR becomes misaligned with assigned timestep, causing error accumulation. Proposes DCW (Differential Correction in Wavelet domain) as a training-free, plug-and-play remedy achieving up to 47.1% FID reduction.

